00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:07,490
and his reign of terror,

274
00:16:07,499 --> 00:16:11,332
meted out to our population
by his police,

275
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:15,337
and especially by a certain
colonel in the force

276
00:16:15,341 --> 00:16:20,301
whose name has become
synonymous with sudden death.

277
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:24,304
Seneca was persecuted
by two tyrants,

278
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:27,318
Caligula and Nero.

279
00:16:27,485 --> 00:16:29,283
In spite of that,

280
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:32,448
Seneca advocated the return
to the Republic...

281
00:16:33,292 --> 00:16:35,452
unafraid.

282
00:16:35,461 --> 00:16:40,421
Mr. Speaker, Seneca,
not the Neros of this world,

283
00:16:41,299 --> 00:16:44,530
should be an example to us.

284
00:16:57,282 --> 00:16:59,442
Fangio, I am your biggest fan.

285
00:16:59,451 --> 00:17:02,283
Get in the car.
Just get in the car.

286
00:17:02,287 --> 00:17:03,413
Get in the car.
Get in.

287
00:17:03,455 --> 00:17:06,288
What do you want? Money?

288
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:07,258
Publicity.

289
00:17:09,461 --> 00:17:11,429
Fangio freed,
Grand Prix cancelled,

290
00:17:11,462 --> 00:17:13,431
26th of July Movement responsible.

291
00:17:14,298 --> 00:17:15,424
And listen to what Fangio said.

292
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:16,365
All they wanted from me

293
00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:18,494
is that I help them
further their cause.

294
00:17:18,503 --> 00:17:22,337
But I don't know anything
about causes, only cars.

295
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:24,338
And when they ask him
how he was treated,

296
00:17:24,509 --> 00:17:26,443
They were quintessential
gentlemen.

297
00:17:27,278 --> 00:17:29,405
Do you think I'm a quintessential
gentleman, Mercedes?

298
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,449
Huh?

299
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:35,277
What was so funny?
What were you laughing about?

300
00:17:35,287 --> 00:17:37,221
The funnies.

301
00:17:37,355 --> 00:17:38,516
The funnies?
That newspaper has no funnies.

302
00:17:40,358 --> 00:17:42,259
Why don't you try the one
about the kidnappers

303
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:43,282
who only wanted publicity?

304
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:44,261
Stop it!

305
00:17:44,462 --> 00:17:46,396
That's funny. That's funny.

306
00:17:46,498 --> 00:17:47,487
Leave him alone! Stop!

307
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:51,358
Yeah. Come on.

308
00:17:51,369 --> 00:17:52,496
Stop! Let him go!

309
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:57,432
Please stop!

310
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:01,344
Stop it! Stop it!

311
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:02,346
Stop it!

312
00:18:13,392 --> 00:18:15,359
Huh?

313
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:16,519
You want to be tough? Huh?

314
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:19,361
Wanna play in my city?

315
00:18:19,364 --> 00:18:20,490
Spoiled rich bastard!

316
00:18:22,366 --> 00:18:25,358
You do not want
to disappoint me.

317
00:18:25,403 --> 00:18:28,338
Believe me.

318
00:18:28,339 --> 00:18:30,307
I'm gonna go for a walk.

319
00:18:30,342 --> 00:18:33,310
When I get back,

320
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:35,471
I want you to tell
me who Peligro is.

321
00:18:43,321 --> 00:18:44,448
I'm back.

322
00:18:46,491 --> 00:18:49,461
Who's Peligro? Huh?

323
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:58,394
You're not a good listener.

324
00:19:00,271 --> 00:19:03,240
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

325
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:20,446
Ooh. No, I'm okay, I'm okay.

326
00:19:20,491 --> 00:19:24,326
I'm gonna go for a walk, okay?

327
00:19:24,328 --> 00:19:26,297
So you better be thinking about
who Peligro is,

328
00:19:26,498 --> 00:19:29,296
'cause you're next.

329
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:32,269
Let's go for some coffee.

330
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:35,296
You're here about your brother.

331
00:19:35,307 --> 00:19:37,240
Your little brother's a criminal

332
00:19:37,276 --> 00:19:39,403
a dangerous criminal.

333
00:19:39,411 --> 00:19:41,241
No doubt about that.

334
00:19:41,279 --> 00:19:43,248
I've got his file
if you wanna read it.

335
00:19:43,281 --> 00:19:45,250
No, thank you.

336
00:19:46,417 --> 00:19:48,249
I know my brother,

337
00:19:48,252 --> 00:19:51,483
and no file will ever change that.

338
00:19:51,522 --> 00:19:56,256
Fico, we've known each other
since we were in prep school.

339
00:19:56,260 --> 00:19:57,386
I've always
been straight with you.

340
00:19:57,395 --> 00:19:58,363
That's true.

341
00:19:58,497 --> 00:20:00,327
Have you ever known me
to change my signals?

342
00:20:00,464 --> 00:20:02,296
Not when you were my catcher.

343
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:04,359
Fico, you're pitching
for your brother now.

344
00:20:04,403 --> 00:20:06,336
You're pitching wild.

345
00:20:06,438 --> 00:20:08,497
He's guilty.
There's no doubt about that.

346
00:20:09,307 --> 00:20:11,434
I know it and you know it.

347
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:14,278
He's my brother, Braulio.

348
00:20:18,416 --> 00:20:20,281
I need your help.

349
00:20:25,289 --> 00:20:26,257
Okay.

350
00:20:27,358 --> 00:20:28,451
I think you should
get out of Havana,

351
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:30,250
go to New York or Miami,

352
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:32,262
and I'm gonna take
care of the tickets.

353
00:20:32,297 --> 00:20:34,265
Fico, Fidel's gonna
take care of me.

354
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:38,269
I'm leaving for
the Sierra Maestra.

355
00:20:38,303 --> 00:20:39,429
Hey.

356
00:20:42,307 --> 00:20:44,275
Fico, I have no choice.

357
00:20:47,445 --> 00:20:49,277
What about your family?

358
00:20:49,314 --> 00:20:52,282
Everything I do
is for my family.

359
00:20:57,321 --> 00:20:58,448
I love you.

360
00:21:12,237 --> 00:21:13,499
Uh, come in.

361
00:21:15,374 --> 00:21:16,363
Can I help you?

362
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:18,343
Al sent me.

363
00:21:18,376 --> 00:21:19,502
Who?

364
00:21:21,512 --> 00:21:23,276
Al.

365
00:21:23,382 --> 00:21:24,508
He's a friend of yours, isn't he?

366
00:21:24,548 --> 00:21:26,346
Are you auditioning?

367
00:21:27,352 --> 00:21:29,319
Yes, I am.

368
00:21:29,354 --> 00:21:30,480
What's your line?

369
00:21:30,521 --> 00:21:31,489
I'm a comedian.

370
00:21:33,458 --> 00:21:36,325
I'm a stand-up comedian

371
00:21:36,361 --> 00:21:39,296
who prefers to remain seated.

372
00:21:39,330 --> 00:21:40,423
That's it?
That's your line?

373
00:21:40,432 --> 00:21:42,229
Yeah.

374
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:44,460
Some jokes for your emcee.

375
00:21:45,269 --> 00:21:46,259
He writes his own jokes.

376
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:48,397
They're lousy. So are yours.

377
00:21:48,406 --> 00:21:50,375
Touch?

378
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:52,433
You want some help writing
some of your other material?

379
00:21:52,443 --> 00:21:55,208
Nobody writes anybody's
material around here.

380
00:21:55,247 --> 00:21:56,338
You just improvise?

381
00:21:56,381 --> 00:21:58,280
You can call it that.
Try New York.

382
00:21:58,282 --> 00:22:01,251
Too cold. Too rich.

383
00:22:01,286 --> 00:22:02,309
Too close to home.

384
00:22:02,453 --> 00:22:04,318
Well, I'm afraid
you're going to have to

385
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:05,381
find another line of work, then.

386
00:22:06,258 --> 00:22:07,316
I can't.

387
00:22:07,358 --> 00:22:10,294
The laughter
you just become addicted to it.

388
00:22:10,295 --> 00:22:12,262
What'd you say your name was?

389
00:22:12,263 --> 00:22:16,461
I didn't.
I said Al sent me.

390
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:20,460
If you know Al, you know me.

391
00:22:21,339 --> 00:22:23,307
Oh, Al's friend.

392
00:22:23,508 --> 00:22:24,474
Where've you been?

393
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,339
Where haven't I been?

394
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:28,313
Federico, remember your
appointment.

395
00:22:28,512 --> 00:22:30,344
And don't forget your dancing
shoes.

396
00:22:30,481 --> 00:22:31,449
You're going to need them.

397
00:22:32,317 --> 00:22:35,308
Oh, Rodney?

398
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:36,480
Maestro?

399
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:40,325
Oh, never mind.

400
00:22:42,493 --> 00:22:46,327
I think I have
a job for you after all.

401
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:48,491
Finally, after all these years

402
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:51,491
of sacrifice and dedication,

403
00:22:51,502 --> 00:22:54,336
a break.

404
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,346
Why can't you tell
me who we're meeting?

405
00:23:02,346 --> 00:23:03,314
It's better that way.

406
00:23:03,347 --> 00:23:04,372
I love surprises.

407
00:23:04,415 --> 00:23:05,440
Just don't say a word

408
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:07,240
no matter what.

409
00:23:07,285 --> 00:23:09,445
Sit there,
pretend you're my security. That's it.

410
00:23:09,453 --> 00:23:11,422
How's this?
Cozy enough?

411
00:23:12,257 --> 00:23:13,416
Look a little bit more dangerous.

412
00:23:13,424 --> 00:23:15,393
How about this?

413
00:23:17,461 --> 00:23:18,291
More dangerous.

414
00:23:19,463 --> 00:23:21,432
This is my meanest.

415
00:23:24,435 --> 00:23:26,267
Save that.

416
00:23:27,305 --> 00:23:28,271
Can I make a wish?

417
00:23:28,306 --> 00:23:29,397
Be my guest.

418
00:23:29,508 --> 00:23:34,444
I wish for a tall, athletic,
caramel-colored beauty.

419
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:35,445
Okay.

420
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:41,478
An open-door policy
is the sign of a great host.

421
00:23:42,319 --> 00:23:44,288
Mr. Lansky, come in.
Welcome.

422
00:23:44,489 --> 00:23:47,321
Should I call you Federico,

423
00:23:47,325 --> 00:23:50,294
Mr. Fellove, or Fico?

424
00:23:52,463 --> 00:23:56,298
Depends on whether
you shake my hand or not.

425
00:23:56,334 --> 00:23:57,460
Call me Fico.

426
00:23:57,469 --> 00:23:59,436
You can call my Meyer.
All my friends do.

427
00:24:00,337 --> 00:24:02,306
Have a seat.

428
00:24:03,474 --> 00:24:04,442
Who is this guy?

429
00:24:04,476 --> 00:24:07,444
Don't mind him,
he's just a comedian.

430
00:24:07,479 --> 00:24:08,445
A blind one?

431
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,446
Mute.

432
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,278
That's funny.

433
00:24:11,282 --> 00:24:12,340
Would you like a drink?

434
00:24:12,483 --> 00:24:16,477
A little seltzer,
unless you happen to, uh...

435
00:24:16,488 --> 00:24:17,454
have an egg cream.

436
00:24:18,289 --> 00:24:19,278
I have eggs and I have cream.

437
00:24:19,423 --> 00:24:20,413
And you have a blind comedian.

438
00:24:20,525 --> 00:24:22,355
Mute.

439
00:24:24,528 --> 00:24:26,394
An egg cream
is neither egg nor cream.

440
00:24:26,431 --> 00:24:28,398
Would you like
to know how to make one?

441
00:24:28,532 --> 00:24:29,500
Well, that would've
been my next question.

442
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:31,428
Well, let? S see
how this goes first.

443
00:24:32,269 --> 00:24:35,261
A little seltzer for now.
Cuts the humidity.

444
00:24:38,442 --> 00:24:40,501
You hear that, comedian?

445
00:24:41,278 --> 00:24:42,439
You said something on the
phone about a business opportunity.

446
00:24:43,248 --> 00:24:46,240
Well played. Le Chaim.

447
00:24:48,452 --> 00:24:51,286
I propose
a partnership between us.

448
00:24:51,288 --> 00:24:54,258
20% goes to the house,

449
00:24:54,291 --> 00:24:56,317
the rest to me, my associates.

450
00:24:56,394 --> 00:24:57,383
It doesn't have
to be anything big.

451
00:24:58,296 --> 00:24:59,422
I mean, this is very cozy here.

452
00:24:59,431 --> 00:25:01,261
You could have a couple of tables,

453
00:25:01,298 --> 00:25:04,426
craps, you know, blackjack,
a wheel or two.

454
00:25:04,435 --> 00:25:06,267
This is nice.

455
00:25:06,304 --> 00:25:08,271
Mr. Lansky

456
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:12,435
Call him Meyer.

457
00:25:13,310 --> 00:25:14,436
Or Mr. Lansky.

458
00:25:15,279 --> 00:25:16,440
You want him here?

459
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:19,442
Meyer, I appreciate the offer,

460
00:25:19,451 --> 00:25:21,351
but, regretfully, I have to pass.

461
00:25:21,452 --> 00:25:24,319
Now, I know this is
a tremendous opportunity for me.

462
00:25:24,321 --> 00:25:27,450
However, El Tropico
is a place of music,

463
00:25:27,459 --> 00:25:29,426
and that's how
I would like it to stay.

464
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:34,423
Let me rephrase.

465
00:25:34,465 --> 00:25:36,297
We have the beginning

466
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:38,291
of a mutually
beneficial relationship.

467
00:25:38,303 --> 00:25:40,430
It would be a pity to see it end
before it even began.

468
00:25:40,471 --> 00:25:41,439
Yes, it would.

469
00:25:41,472 --> 00:25:43,441
All right.

470
00:25:47,479 --> 00:25:51,346
I was informed
you were a reasonable man.

471
00:25:51,449 --> 00:25:53,314
I hope I wasn't misinformed.

472
00:25:53,317 --> 00:25:54,285
You weren't.

473
00:25:54,451 --> 00:25:56,442
What I can offer you in return

474
00:25:56,488 --> 00:25:58,455
is what I offer all my friends

475
00:25:58,490 --> 00:26:00,458
an open-door policy.

476
00:26:01,326 --> 00:26:03,351
Consider my club
your home any time.

477
00:26:03,528 --> 00:26:05,461
What, free seltzer?

478
00:26:05,462 --> 00:26:08,227
As much as you want.

479
00:26:08,266 --> 00:26:10,233
You know, in my business,
Mr. Fellove,

480
00:26:10,434 --> 00:26:12,403
we have friends
and we have enemies,

481
00:26:13,305 --> 00:26:15,397
but we don't
have acquaintances.

482
00:26:17,241 --> 00:26:20,369
I hope to hear
some good news very soon.

483
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:34,384
Is that Meyer Lansky...
Meyer Lansky?

484
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:36,359
The head of the mob.

485
00:26:36,394 --> 00:26:38,224
I resign.

486
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:03,253
Are you wearing false eyelashes,
or are you truly bashful?

487
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:04,413
I never wear false eyelashes.

488
00:27:04,422 --> 00:27:05,354
That's my girl.

489
00:27:06,523 --> 00:27:07,490
Am I?

490
00:27:30,347 --> 00:27:31,440
Whose idea was that?

491
00:27:31,482 --> 00:27:33,473
Rodney's.

492
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:37,480
Are you gonna be watching?

493
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:40,321
Always.

494
00:28:12,356 --> 00:28:14,325
What's the matter?

495
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:20,330
What's wrong?

496
00:28:20,330 --> 00:28:22,458
Luis has another woman.

497
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:24,297
Another woman?

498
00:28:28,306 --> 00:28:32,241
He hasn't come home in two days,

499
00:28:32,242 --> 00:28:36,373
and before that, we haven't

500
00:28:36,413 --> 00:28:38,507
His mind is elsewhere.

501
00:28:40,484 --> 00:28:42,281
Has he called?

502
00:28:42,453 --> 00:28:44,354
Just to say that he's okay,

503
00:28:44,388 --> 00:28:46,516
and that's all he says.

504
00:28:48,358 --> 00:28:51,259
Fico, help me.

505
00:28:51,395 --> 00:28:54,387
You're the only one
I can turn to.

506
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:56,365
I'm gonna take care of it.

507
00:29:22,259 --> 00:29:24,421
She's worried about you.

508
00:29:28,298 --> 00:29:29,424
She came to you?

509
00:29:33,270 --> 00:29:34,431
She's always had a...

510
00:29:36,473 --> 00:29:39,340
very special place
in her heart for you.

511
00:29:39,376 --> 00:29:41,470
And you for her.

512
00:29:41,479 --> 00:29:44,448
What's the matter? Talk to me.

513
00:29:44,481 --> 00:29:47,315
I'm not gonna get you involved.

514
00:29:47,352 --> 00:29:50,480
I'm your brother. I'm involved.
What's up?

515
00:29:50,488 --> 00:29:52,318
Is it another woman?

516
00:29:52,323 --> 00:29:53,289
Yes.

517
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:58,258
Liberty.

518
00:30:21,352 --> 00:30:23,319
You involved with Fidel?
No.

519
00:30:23,354 --> 00:30:25,321
26th of July Movement,
like Ricardo?

520
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:26,289
No.

521
00:30:28,259 --> 00:30:31,422
Directorio Revolucionario.

522
00:30:31,429 --> 00:30:33,396
We're no longer associated.

523
00:30:33,431 --> 00:30:36,400
We have our own ideas for Cuba.

524
00:30:37,268 --> 00:30:39,394
Pluralism,

525
00:30:39,403 --> 00:30:41,372
the restoration of
the 1940 Constitution.

526
00:30:42,272 --> 00:30:43,240
You know, democracy.

527
00:30:43,273 --> 00:30:44,400
That's what Fidel says he wants.

528
00:30:44,409 --> 00:30:47,377
Sure, that's what he says,
but he can't be trusted.

529
00:30:47,412 --> 00:30:50,381
You think he's a Communist?

530
00:30:50,414 --> 00:30:51,507
A Fidelista.

531
00:30:58,388 --> 00:31:00,481
You have to promise me something.

532
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:01,491
What?

533
00:31:04,494 --> 00:31:06,326
Anything happens to me...

534
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,526
you'll look after Aurora.

535
00:31:13,304 --> 00:31:15,295
She'll need you.

536
00:31:15,306 --> 00:31:16,432
Here, promise me.

537
00:31:19,277 --> 00:31:21,244
Promise me, Fico.

538
00:31:22,413 --> 00:31:25,382
I need this from you.

539
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:27,442
I promise you.

540
00:31:28,286 --> 00:31:29,252
But you're gonna promise me

541
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:32,346
that nothing's gonna
happen to you, right?

542
00:31:32,490 --> 00:31:34,423
Right?

543
00:31:34,424 --> 00:31:38,259
There's no happiness
outside the revolution.

544
00:31:47,538 --> 00:31:49,506
Okay.

545
00:31:54,378 --> 00:31:57,279
Don't do something stupid.

546
00:31:57,281 --> 00:31:59,272
Okay?

547
00:32:33,384 --> 00:32:36,511
Ricardo Fellove,
26th of July Movement.

