01:00:14,277 --> 01:00:15,402
There he is.

824
01:02:10,326 --> 01:02:13,318
How many more are in the barracks?

825
01:02:13,362 --> 01:02:14,487
Come on. Come on.

826
01:02:14,496 --> 01:02:16,327
How many more are in the barracks?

827
01:02:18,501 --> 01:02:20,492
Fellove!

828
01:02:20,503 --> 01:02:24,496
Let's move. Don't waste
any time with that.

829
01:02:24,539 --> 01:02:25,507
Let's move.

830
01:02:29,512 --> 01:02:31,309
You seem troubled, Fellove.

831
01:02:33,416 --> 01:02:35,384
Is it about the captain we shot?

832
01:02:36,251 --> 01:02:38,516
Listen to me very carefully.

833
01:02:38,521 --> 01:02:40,318
In an insurrection,

834
01:02:40,356 --> 01:02:42,324
the end justifies the means.

835
01:02:44,293 --> 01:02:45,418
What is an insurrection?

836
01:02:45,460 --> 01:02:47,394
Huh?

837
01:02:47,429 --> 01:02:48,396
Armed struggle.

838
01:02:50,266 --> 01:02:51,358
What is the end?

839
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:52,425
Revolution.

840
01:02:52,467 --> 01:02:56,403
Which entails social, economic,
and political transformations.

841
01:02:58,273 --> 01:02:59,240
Like I said?

842
01:03:00,409 --> 01:03:03,434
The end justifies the means.

843
01:03:03,445 --> 01:03:05,277
Hmm?

844
01:04:51,454 --> 01:04:52,420
This is Havana.

845
01:04:55,490 --> 01:04:57,458
Who said a woman
is like a flower?

846
01:04:58,327 --> 01:05:00,295
A poet with a sense of smell.

847
01:05:07,469 --> 01:05:09,460
May I join you?

848
01:05:09,472 --> 01:05:11,302
Yes.

849
01:05:19,282 --> 01:05:21,340
What was your name again?

850
01:05:21,349 --> 01:05:24,318
My name again is no name.

851
01:05:24,320 --> 01:05:25,445
What do you mean?

852
01:05:25,487 --> 01:05:27,456
I don't mean nothing!

853
01:05:29,492 --> 01:05:32,460
Names don't mean, people do.

854
01:05:32,460 --> 01:05:35,429
But you are people, aren't you?

855
01:05:36,264 --> 01:05:41,293
That... nobody can deny.

856
01:05:41,304 --> 01:05:43,271
So what's your name, then?

857
01:05:44,472 --> 01:05:46,304
I have no name.

858
01:05:46,309 --> 01:05:48,402
I already told you that.

859
01:05:48,443 --> 01:05:50,275
Everybody has a name.

860
01:05:50,278 --> 01:05:53,407
Mm-hmm.
Everybody but me.

861
01:05:53,449 --> 01:05:54,416
Why not?

862
01:06:00,422 --> 01:06:02,253
I don't know.

863
01:06:02,291 --> 01:06:04,259
Ask him.

864
01:06:04,293 --> 01:06:05,260
Leave me out of your puns.

865
01:06:07,429 --> 01:06:10,228
You're the strangest man
I ever met.

866
01:06:18,541 --> 01:06:19,507
Thank you.

867
01:06:22,378 --> 01:06:23,344
Thank you.

868
01:06:24,547 --> 01:06:26,344
Okay, Emilio.

869
01:06:27,449 --> 01:06:28,507
Your moneys no good here.

870
01:06:29,351 --> 01:06:31,320
Thank you, Emilio.

871
01:06:31,353 --> 01:06:32,320
I'll see you at the club.

872
01:06:34,356 --> 01:06:35,324
When I grow up,

873
01:06:35,490 --> 01:06:37,288
I wanna be just like him.

874
01:06:38,393 --> 01:06:40,362
Why?

875
01:06:41,230 --> 01:06:42,492
Because...

876
01:06:42,530 --> 01:06:44,327
he never pays.

877
01:06:51,507 --> 01:06:55,443
we interrupt
this program with a special news report.

878
01:06:58,514 --> 01:07:02,280
The University of Havana was
closed by the government today,

879
01:07:02,318 --> 01:07:05,309
as a direct result
of the ongoing riots.

880
01:07:05,320 --> 01:07:06,447
President Fulgencio Batista,

881
01:07:06,489 --> 01:07:08,456
who is under intense pressure
to resign,

882
01:07:08,490 --> 01:07:10,458
declared publicly today
that the government

883
01:07:10,492 --> 01:07:13,518
will not tolerate the disgracing
of the sacred grounds

884
01:07:13,528 --> 01:07:15,496
of the university's Plaza Cadena,

885
01:07:15,530 --> 01:07:18,500
which he claims the professional
agitators were using

886
01:07:18,534 --> 01:07:21,367
for their selfish acts of anarchy.

887
01:08:02,545 --> 01:08:03,512
She wants to talk to you.

888
01:08:04,547 --> 01:08:05,514
It's okay.

889
01:08:07,550 --> 01:08:10,451
El tiempo no estacon ustedes.

890
01:08:14,255 --> 01:08:15,347
What did she say?

891
01:08:15,523 --> 01:08:17,492
Time is not on our side.

